    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>soaked ginger</strong>, then add it to a bowl with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the<strong> salad</strong> to the bowl and give everything a gentle mix up – this is your <strong>quick-pickled ginger salad</strong></p><p>On a clean board, slice the <strong>breaded</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> finely into strips – this is your <strong>chicken katsu</strong></p>",
